<h2 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=E2=9A=A13.GraphTerminology">=E2=9A=A1 <str=
ong>3. Graph Terminology</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"ffd30b0e-af50-493b-b25d-472=
d1e89ff11" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Term</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Definition</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Vertex (Node)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A point in a graph</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Edge (Link)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Connection between vertices</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Degree</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Number of edges incident to a vertex</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>In-degree / Out-degree</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>For directed graphs, incoming/outgoing edges</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Path</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Sequence of edges connecting vertices</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Cycle</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Path that starts and ends at same vertex</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Connected Graph</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>There is a path between any two vertices</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Disconnected Graph</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Some vertices cannot be reached from others</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Subgraph</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A graph formed from a subset of vertices and edges</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Adjacency</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Two vertices are adjacent if they share an edge</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=94=B94.SpecialGraphs">=F0=9F=94=B9 <=
strong>4. Special Graphs</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Tree</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A connected, acyclic graph</p></li>
<li>
<p>Properties:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>n vertices =E2=86=92 n-1 edges</p></li>
<li>
<p>One unique path between any two vertices</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Spanning Tree</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A subgraph that includes all vertices of original graph and is a tree</p=
></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Complete Graph</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Every pair of vertices is connected by an edge</p></li>
<li>
<p>Number of edges: ( E =3D \frac{n(n-1)}{2} )</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Bipartite Graph</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Vertex set divided into two disjoint sets U and V</p></li>
<li>
<p>No edge connects vertices within the same set</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=E2=9A=A15.RepresentationofGraphs">=E2=9A=
=A1 <strong>5. Representation of Graphs</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Adjacency Matrix</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>n =C3=97 n matrix A</p></li>
<li>
<p>A[i][j] =3D 1 if edge exists between vertex i and j, else 0</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Adjacency List</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Each vertex has a list of connected vertices</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Incidence Matrix</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Rows =3D vertices, columns =3D edges</p></li>
<li>
<p>A[i][j] =3D 1 if vertex i is incident on edge j</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=94=B96.GraphOperationsandConcepts">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>6. Graph Operations and Concepts</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Degree of a vertex:</strong> number of edges connected</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Path:</strong> sequence of edges from one vertex to another</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><strong>Cycle:</strong> path starting and ending at same vertex</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Connectedness:</strong> whether all vertices are reachable</p></=
li>
<li>
<p><strong>Components:</strong> maximal connected subgraphs in a disconnect=
ed graph</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=E2=9C=857.ApplicationsofGraphTheory">=E2=
=9C=85 <strong>7. Applications of Graph Theory</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Computer networks (routing, packet delivery)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Social networks (friendship, followers)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Circuit design</p></li>
<li>
<p>Scheduling problems</p></li>
<li>
<p>Shortest path algorithms (Dijkstra, Bellman-Ford)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Compiler design, dependency graphs</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-Inshort:.1"><strong>In short:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>graph</strong> is a collection of vertices and edges.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Graphs can be <strong>directed, undirected, weighted, or unweighted</str=
ong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Trees, bipartite graphs, and complete graphs are special types of graphs=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Representation</strong>: adjacency matrix, adjacency list, incid=
ence matrix.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Widely used in <strong>algorithms, networking, and computer science prob=
lems</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>If you want, I can next explain <strong>Propositional Logic, Predicate L=
ogic, and Boolean Algebra</strong>, which are also core parts of <strong>Di=
screte Mathematics</strong> for government IT exams.</p>
<ol start=3D"4">
<li>
<p>Propositional calculus and predicate calculus;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Let=E2=80=99s explain <strong>Propositional Calculus</strong> and <stron=
g>Predicate Calculus</strong>, which are fundamental in <strong>Discrete Ma=
thematics and Logic</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=A7=A91.PropositionalCalculus(Proposi=
tionalLogic)">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>1. Propositional Calculus (Propositional=
 Logic)</strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=94=B9Definition.2">=F0=9F=94=B9 Defi=
nition</h3>
<p>Propositional logic deals with <strong>propositions</strong> =E2=80=94 s=
tatements that are <strong>either true or false</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Example:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9CIt is raining=E2=80=9D =E2=86=92 proposition P</p></li>
<li>
<p>=E2=80=9C2 + 2 =3D 4=E2=80=9D =E2=86=92 proposition Q</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Connectives</strong> are used to form complex statements from si=
mple propositions.</p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=94=B9LogicalConnectives">=F0=9F=94=
=B9 Logical Connectives</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"da30d524-c460-41ba-9979-b83=
ee3b52bc5" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Connective</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Symbol</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Truth Table</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Negation</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>=C2=ACP</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>NOT P</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>T=E2=86=92F, F=E2=86=92T</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Conjunction</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P =E2=88=A7 Q</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>AND</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>T=E2=88=A7T=3DT, else F</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Disjunction</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P =E2=88=A8 Q</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>OR</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F=E2=88=A7F=3DF, else T</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Exclusive OR</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P =E2=8A=95 Q</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>XOR</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>True if exactly one is true</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Implication</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P =E2=86=92 Q</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>IF P THEN Q</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F=E2=86=92T=3DT, T=E2=86=92F=3DF</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Biconditional</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P =E2=86=94 Q</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>P IF AND ONLY IF Q</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>T=E2=86=94T=3DT, F=E2=86=94F=3DT, else F</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=94=B9LawsofPropositionalLogic">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 Laws of Propositional Logic</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Commutative Law:</strong> P =E2=88=A7 Q =3D Q =E2=88=A7 P; P =E2=
=88=A8 Q =3D Q =E2=88=A8 P</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Associative Law:</strong> (P =E2=88=A7 Q) =E2=88=A7 R =3D P =E2=
=88=A7 (Q =E2=88=A7 R)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Distributive Law:</strong> P =E2=88=A7 (Q =E2=88=A8 R) =3D (P =
=E2=88=A7 Q) =E2=88=A8 (P =E2=88=A7 R)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Identity Law:</strong> P =E2=88=A7 T =3D P; P =E2=88=A8 F =3D P<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Domination Law:</strong> P =E2=88=A7 F =3D F; P =E2=88=A8 T =3D =
T</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>De Morgan=E2=80=99s Laws:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>=C2=AC(P =E2=88=A7 Q) =3D =C2=ACP =E2=88=A8 =C2=ACQ</p></li>
<li>
<p>=C2=AC(P =E2=88=A8 Q) =3D =C2=ACP =E2=88=A7 =C2=ACQ</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=94=B9Applications">=F0=9F=94=B9 Appl=
ications</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Digital circuits (AND, OR, NOT gates)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Programming conditions (if-else statements)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Proving logical equivalence and correctness of algorithms</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=A7=A92.PredicateCalculus(First-Order=
Logic)">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>2. Predicate Calculus (First-Order Logic)</str=
ong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=94=B9Definition.3">=F0=9F=94=B9 Defi=
nition</h3>
<p>Predicate logic extends propositional logic by including <strong>quantif=
iers, variables, and predicates</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Predicate: Property or relation involving variables</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Example: P(x): =E2=80=9Cx is even=E2=80=9D</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Quantifiers: express statements over <strong>all</strong> or <strong>som=
e elements</strong> of a domain</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"C_DiscreteMathematics-=F0=9F=94=B9Quantifiers">=F0=9F=94=B9 Quant=
ifiers</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"330365fb-8196-43c0-96ff-08d=
ad4436466" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Quantifier</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Symbol</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Universal</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>=E2=88=80x</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>=E2=80=9CFor all x=E2=80=9D</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>=E2=88=80x =E2=88=88 =E2=84=95, x+0 =3D x</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Existential</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
